# GITHUB DEPLOYMENT RULE

## REPOSITORY INFORMATION

- **REPOSITORY URL**: https://github.com/igarikg/Tetris.git
- **BRANCH**: main
- **GIT PATH**: "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe"

## DEPLOYMENT WORKFLOW

WHEN THE USER REQUESTS TO DEPLOY, PUSH, OR UPDATE THE GITHUB REPOSITORY, FOLLOW THESE STEPS:

### 1. CHECK STATUS
```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" status
```

### 2. STAGE CHANGES
```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" add .
```

### 3. CREATE COMMIT
```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" commit -m "YOUR COMMIT MESSAGE IN CAPITALS"
```

### 4. PUSH TO GITHUB
```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" push origin main
```

## COMMIT MESSAGE GUIDELINES

- USE CAPITAL LETTERS FOR ALL COMMIT MESSAGES (FOLLOWING PROJECT CONVENTION)
- BE DESCRIPTIVE BUT CONCISE
- EXAMPLES:
  - "ADD NEW FEATURE: PAUSE FUNCTIONALITY"
  - "FIX BUG: COLLISION DETECTION"
  - "UPDATE STYLES: GAME BOARD COLORS"

## QUICK DEPLOYMENT COMMAND

FOR QUICK DEPLOYMENTS, USE A SINGLE COMMAND:
```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" add . ; & "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" commit -m "UPDATE" ; & "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" push origin main
```

## NOTES

- ALWAYS CHECK `git status` BEFORE COMMITTING
- IF PUSH FAILS, CHECK INTERNET CONNECTION AND GITHUB AUTHENTICATION
- USE FULL PATH TO GIT EXECUTABLE IN POWERSHELL UNTIL PATH IS REFRESHED
